A fully manual neural network implementation developed for my university project. This project includes weight initialization, forward propagation, backpropagation, sigmoid activation, gradient computation, and parameter updates implemented from scratch without using machine learning frameworks.
A lightweight, feature-engineered machine learning framework (FEIIDS) for real-time IoT intrusion detection, ensuring high accuracy and low computational cost.

The retention of computer science graduates in the technology workforce remains a critical challenge, especially in developing countries like Bangladesh. This study proposes a machine learning-based framework to predict programmer retention by analyzing socio-economic, academic and motivational factors. Using data from Bangladeshi Universities

This project Predicts plant health using NDVI values, classifying leaves as Healthy, Unhealthy, or Dead. NDVI drives prediction, while OpenCV showcases image color and edges, and CNN (MobileNetV2) extracts features for visualization. Includes EDA plots for NDVI distribution and category analysis in a concise, educational framework.

A high-performance data processing engine built with Rust, designed for modern machine learning workflows. Zi provides a unified framework for data quality assessment, cleaning, transformation, sampling, and augmentation with exceptional speed and reliability.

This project presents a practical approach to improving retail inventory accuracy using data-driven forecasting. By combining statistical models, modern machine-learning techniques, and reinforcement learning, the study builds a structured framework capable of predicting demand, planning reorder cycles, and reducing supply-chain inefficiencies.

HackGPT Enterprise is a production-ready, cloud-native AI-powered penetration testing platform designed for enterprise security teams. It combines advanced AI, machine learning, microservices architecture, and comprehensive security frameworks to deliver professional-grade cybersecurity assessments.

A full-stack SaaS platform built from scratch, integrating modern machine learning frameworks with scalable cloud infrastructure. Includes production-ready ML pipelines, automated data processing workflows, and real-time predictive analytics for end-user applications.

This repo features the code, input and output files for my undergraduate thesis titled "Design and optimization of an integrated computational and machine learning framework to detect functional variants and elucidate their contributions to biological pathways".

This project presents an AI-Driven IoT Framework designed to automate the process of fruit detection, ripeness classification, and autonomous plucking in modern smart farms. By integrating computer vision, machine learning, robotic control, and IoT connectivity, the system aims to improve harvesting efficiency, reduce labor dependency.

A machine-learning framework that predicts Ultimate Tensile Strength (UTS) of steels using composition + heat-treatment + processing parameters. The dataset is synthetically generated using metallurgy-based rules (HallPetch, tempering response, quenching behavior, composition strengthening).

This repository provides an end-to-end workflow integrating differential expression analysis, machine learningbased feature selection, survival modelling, and external biological validation for robust biomarker discovery.

This repository contains a complete, end-to-end research framework for understanding how monetary liquidity regimes shape equity valuations, factor returns, and market dynamics. The project combines macro-finance theory, econometric modeling, and modern machine learning methods to build a structural interpretation of liquidity-driven markets.
A demo project for TensorFlow. TensorFlow is an open-source machine learning (ML) and deep learning (DL) framework developed by Google.

Machine Learning framework for PWR abnormality detection using an optimized Random Forest model with SMOTE balancing and Grid Search tuning. Includes full evaluation, ROC-AUC, confusion matrix, feature importance, and reproducible code from the research publication.

A full-stack website built using the React and FastAPI frameworks, utilizing machine learning to recommend comics based on previous ratings.

This repository contains my personal projects and experiments in Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning. My goal is to build a strong foundation in AI/ML by experimenting, learning, and sharing my progress with the community.

CareMate is a research initiative exploring the ethical intersection of machine learning and homeopathy. It has evolved from a simple urgency predictor into a comprehensive, privacy-first triage framework.  The system combines Explainable AI like SHAP/LIME.

Face Recognition System using MediaPipe - demonstrating that "Every AI is not ML". Includes dataset creation, review, model training, and real-time prediction capabilities. Built with Python 3.10-3.12.6.
